title: Macomb Team
text: I went in for treatment after my lower back went out, never happened before. I had to say the entire process was slower than I thought. I figured I’d be back to full activities in a month. They ensured me it was a process. I was confused as to why they were working  on parts other than my lower back. Hamstring, quads. Calves,.glutes. They explained that the back pain is connected other areas. While working on the back they give you the tools going forward with hopes of preventing reoccurrence. You also have to do the homework as part of the process but it works. I’m thankful to not have been back for treatment.  Thank you keep up the good work!

title: Dr. Modiri
text:
Dr. Modiri is a wonderful gastroenterologist in Woodbridge, VA. Having had multiple colonoscopies by other providers, there is no comparison to her skill, efficiency, patience, kindness, thorough explanations and amazing bedside manner. I was in and out in 1 hour. Her staff was amazing, the best office staff I have ever experienced. Having come from another large GI practice with none of these qualities, I am very grateful.
And I have worked in health care for 40 years.

title: 25 years
text: I’ve been going to the State Street location for over 25 years. The same guy has been there for most of the time. Steve, has taken great care of all my vehicles. In over 100 visits, there was only once when I wasn’t satisfied. A new technician forgot to torque my oil plug and lied about greasing my driveline. I only drove as far as Albertsons. I was checking to see if the kid greased my chassis and discovered the oil trail. The technician was immediately fired and I was all set in 5 minutes. Ever since then I’ve been a loyal customer.
